collections.name: current_terms

properties.name: address
properties.description: The address of this legislator.

properties.name: bioguide
properties.description: The alphanumeric ID for this legislator.

properties.name: caucus
properties.description: For independents, the party that the legislator caucuses with. This field is what normally determines committee seniority.

properties.name: chamber
properties.description: The chamber where the legislator serves. Values: senate, house.

properties.name: class_
properties.description: For senators, their election class (1, 2, or 3).

extra semantic info.commonsense evidence: Only senators have a class. If the value is null or empty, this legislator is not a senator.

properties.name: contact_form
properties.description: The website URL of the contact page on the legislator's official website.

properties.name: district
properties.description: For representatives, the district number they are serving from.

extra semantic info.commonsense evidence: If null or empty, they are not representatives.

properties.name: end_
properties.description: The date the term ended. This is the last date on which the legislator served this term.

properties.name: fax
properties.description: The fax number of the legislator's Washington, D.C. office.

extra semantic info.validity: Only valid if the term is current.

properties.name: last
properties.description: The last known phone/fax number.

properties.name: name
properties.description: Not a useful column.

properties.name: office
properties.description: The legislator's office address.

extra semantic info.validity: Only valid if the term is current, otherwise the last known office.

properties.name: party
properties.description: The political party of the legislator. Values are typically 'Democrat', 'Independent', or 'Republican'.

extra semantic info.commonsense evidence: If the legislator changed parties, this is the most recent party held during the term and party_affiliations will be set. The value typically matches the political party of the legislator on the ballot in his or her last election, although for state affiliate parties such as 'Democratic Farmer Labor' we will use the national party name ('Democrat') instead to keep the values of this field normalized.

properties.name: party_affiliations
properties.description: A list of time periods of party affiliations, present if the legislator changed party or caucus affiliation during the term.

properties.name: phone
properties.description: The phone number of the legislator's Washington, D.C. office.

extra semantic info.validity: Only valid if the term is current, otherwise the last known number.

properties.name: relation
properties.description: Not a useful column.

properties.name: rss_url
properties.description: The URL to the official website's RSS feed.

properties.name: start
properties.description: The date legislative service began for this term.

properties.name: state
properties.description: The two-letter state code for the state the legislator represents.

properties.name: state_rank
properties.description: For senators, whether they are the 'junior' or 'senior' senator.

extra semantic info.validity: Only valid if the term is current, otherwise it reflects the senator's rank at the time the term ended.
extra semantic info.commonsense evidence: Only senators have this value.

properties.name: title
properties.description: The title of the legislator (e.g., Minority Whip, Speaker).

properties.name: type_
properties.description: The type of the term. Either 'sen' for senators or 'rep' for representatives and delegates to the House.

properties.name: url
properties.description: The official website URL of the legislator.

extra semantic info.validity: Only valid if the term is current.

collections.description: Contains information about the terms served by current legislators.

extra semantic info.census_divisions: Further information on the 9 divisions of states can be found at https://www2.census.gov/geo/pdfs/maps-data/maps/reference/us_regdiv.pdf
